Decomposes as within-component variance plus between-component variance:

$$
\operatorname{Var}[X] = \underbrace{\sum_k \pi_k \sigma_k^2}_{\text{within}}
                       + \underbrace{\sum_k \pi_k (\mu_k - E[X])^2}_{\text{between}}
$$

$$
H[X] = \tfrac{D}{2}(1 + \log(2\pi)) + \sum_i \log L_{ii}
$$

$$
\mathbb{E}[X] = e^{\mu + \sigma^2/2}
$$

$$
\text{Var}[X] = (e^{\sigma^2} - 1)\,e^{2\mu + \sigma^2}
$$

parameters.description:
Temperature parameter $\tau > 0$.  Controls the sharpness
of the relaxation.  Small values give near-discrete samples;
large values give near-uniform samples.

