Returns $-\log(b - a)$ inside the support $[a, b)$ and
$-\infty$ outside:

$$
\log p(x; a, b) = \begin{cases}
    -\log(b - a) & x \in [a, b) \\
    -\infty & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
$$
